EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to elections; requiring a county or city clerk to
provide certain information or data relating to the current
election cycle within a certain period of time; revising
qualifications for certain elected public officers to require
such officers to be registered to vote in this State; revising
provisions governing a declaration of candidacy and
declaration of residency; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Section 1 of this bill provides that if the Secretary of State requests any
2 information or data relating to the current election cycle from a county or city clerk,
3 the clerk is required, not later than the end of the second working day after
4 receiving the request, to provide the Secretary of State with: (1) the information or
5 data; or (2) a written explanation that indicates when the county or city clerk will
6 reasonably be able to provide the information or data.
7 Existing law requires a person to be a qualified elector to be eligible for a
8 public office in this State. (Nev. Const. Art. 15, § 3) Existing law also requires,
9 with certain exceptions, a candidate for any elected office to actually, as opposed to
10 constructively, reside in the State, district, county, township or other area
11 prescribed by law to which the office pertains. (NRS 293.1755) Sections 2 and 7-
12 77 of this bill include as a qualification for any elected public office other than
13 federal office, including, without limitation, State Legislator, Governor, Lieutenant
14 Governor, Attorney General, Secretary of State, State Treasurer, State Controller,
15 county commissioners, county clerk, sheriff, district attorney, public administrator,
16 city council, mayor, the Board of Regents of the University of Nevada, the board of
-
