17 directors of a general improvement district and the board of directors of a water
18 district, that the officer be registered to vote in the State, district, county, township
19 or other area prescribed by law to which the officer is required to reside. Section 78
20 of this bill provides that the requirement for these officers to be registered to vote in
21 this State does not apply to a person who, on October 1, 2025, holds such office.
22 Existing law requires a candidate for a primary election for a public office to
23 file a declaration of candidacy and a candidate for the office of State Senator,
24 Assemblyman or Assemblywoman to also file a declaration of residency. (NRS
25 293.177, 293.181, 293C.185) Existing law also requires a person nominated or
26 applying to fill a vacancy in the office of Legislator to file a declaration of
27 eligibility with the board of county commissioners. (NRS 218A.264) Sections 3, 4,
28 6 and 13 of this bill provide that a declaration of candidacy, a declaration of
29 residency and a declaration of eligibility are public records and the filing officer
30 must make such declarations available to the public in an electronic format.
31 Sections 3, 6 and 13 also require a person filing a declaration of candidacy or
32 declaration of eligibility to attest under penalty of perjury to the city or town and
33 county of the State of Nevada where the person is registered to vote.
